race.description: Total Comfort Plumbing Services Maiden Plate
race.comment: SILENT ANSWER (13) ran well when fourth behind a smart one on debut then chased hard last time out in a race dominated by the leader. She beat the rest easily. With those two runs under the belt and up to this seemingly suitable distance she gets her chance to break through. STORM LEOPARD (11) did not have a lot go right on debut when hard in the market and he draws for a much more economical run this time. Being a son of Ghaiyyath, the step up in trip will also be of advantage. KING MAYWIN (4) did finish just ahead of STORM LEOPARD last time and while he had a better run that day, he's again drawn to advantage. GOLD CHARIOT (3) is on debut over 1530m, so he's going to be better over further later in his career but comes here off a solid recent jumpout second placing and is from a stable that has a solid record with Kiwi recruits.
